712

716 
717 #ifdef FREERTOS

756 prim ATH_dump() {
757  Sl(2); // address len
758 
759  int length = S0;
760  uint8_t *address = (uint8_t *) S1;
761  int lines=length/16;
762 
763  if(lines ==0 ) {
764  lines=1;
765  }
766 #ifdef FREERTOS
767  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)"\r\n") ;
768 #endif
769 
770  int i=0;
771  for( i = 0; i<length;i+=16) {
772 #ifdef EMBEDDED
773  sprintf(outBuffer,"%08x:", (uintptr_t)address);
774 #endif
775 #ifdef FREERTOS
776  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
777 #else
778  printf("%s", outBuffer);
779 #endif
780  displayLineHex( address );
781  displayLineAscii( address );
782  address +=16;
783  }
784 
785  Pop2;
786 }

831 int8_t readLineFromArray(uint8_t *src, uint8_t *dest) {

1949 /* TOKEN -- Scan a token and return its type. */
1950 
1951 static int token( char **cp) {
1952  char *sp = *cp;
1953 
1954  while (True) {
1955  char *tp = tokbuf;
1956  int tl = 0;
1957  Boolean istring = False, rstring = False;
1958 
1959  if (atl_comment) {
1960  while (*sp != ')') {
1961  if (*sp == EOS) {
1962  *cp = sp;
1963  return TokNull;
1964  }
1965  sp++;
1966  }
1967  sp++;
1968  atl_comment = Falsity;
1969  }
1970 
1971  while (isspace(*sp)) /* Skip leading blanks */
1972  sp++;
1973 
1974  if (*sp == '"') { /* Is this a string ? */
1975 
1976  /* Assemble string token. */
1977 
1978  sp++;
1979  while (True) {
1980  char c = *sp++;
1981 
1982  if (c == '"') {
1983  sp++;
1984  *tp++ = EOS;
1985  break;
1986  } else if (c == EOS) {
1987  rstring = True;
1988  *tp++ = EOS;
1989  break;
1990  }
1991  if (c == '\\') {
1992  c = *sp++;
1993  if (c == EOS) {
1994  rstring = True;
1995  break;
1996  }
1997  switch (c) {
1998  case 'b':
1999  c = '\b';
2000  break;
2001  case 'n':
2002  c = '\n';
2003  break;
2004  case 'r':
2005  c = '\r';
2006  break;
2007  case 't':
2008  c = '\t';
2009  break;
2010  default:
2011  break;
2012  }
2013  }
2014  if (tl < (sizeof tokbuf) - 1) {
2015  *tp++ = c;
2016  tl++;
2017  } else {
2018  rstring = True;
2019  }
2020  }
2021  istring = True;
2022  } else {
2023 
2024  /* Scan the next raw token */
2025 
2026  while (True) {
2027  char c = *sp++;
2028 
2029  if (c == EOS || isspace(c)) {
2030  *tp++ = EOS;
2031  break;
2032  }
2033  if (tl < (sizeof tokbuf) - 1) {
2034  *tp++ = c;
2035  tl++;
2036  }
2037  }
2038  }
2039  *cp = --sp; /* Store end of scan pointer */
2040 
2041  if (istring) {
2042  if (rstring) {
2043 #ifdef MEMMESSAGE
2044 #ifdef EMBEDDED
2045  sprintf(outBuffer,"\nRunaway string: %s\n", tokbuf); // EMBEDDED
2046 #endif
2047 #ifdef FREERTOS
2048  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
2049 #else
2050  printf("%s",outBuffer);
2051 #endif
2052 #endif
2053  evalstat = ATL_RUNSTRING;
2054  return TokNull;
2055  }
2056  return TokString;
2057  }
2058 
2059  if (tokbuf[0] == EOS)
2060  return TokNull;
2061 
2062  /* See if token is a comment to end of line character. If so, discard
2063  the rest of the line and return null for this token request. */
2064 
2065  if (strcmp(tokbuf, "\\") == 0) {
2066  while (*sp != EOS)
2067  sp++;
2068  *cp = sp;
2069  return TokNull;
2070  }
2071 
2072  /* See if this token is a comment open delimiter. If so, set to
2073  ignore all characters until the matching comment close delimiter. */
2074 
2075  if (strcmp(tokbuf, "(") == 0) {
2076  while (*sp != EOS) {
2077  if (*sp == ')')
2078  break;
2079  sp++;
2080  }
2081  if (*sp == ')') {
2082  sp++;
2083  continue;
2084  }
2085  atl_comment = Truth;
2086  *cp = sp;
2087  return TokNull;
2088  }
2089 
2090  /* See if the token is a number. */
2091 
2092  if (isdigit(tokbuf[0]) || tokbuf[0] == '-') {
2093  char tc;
2094  char *tcp;
2095 
2096 #ifdef USE_SSCANF
2097  if (sscanf(tokbuf, "%li%c", &tokint, &tc) == 1)
2098  return TokInt;
2099 #else
2100  tokint = strtoul(tokbuf, &tcp, 0);
2101  if (*tcp == 0) {
2102  return TokInt;
2103  }
2104 #endif
2105 #ifdef REAL
2106  if (sscanf(tokbuf, "%lf%c", &tokreal, &tc) == 1)
2107  return TokReal;
2108 #endif
2109  }
2110  return TokWord;
2111  }
2112 }

2177  V ungetc(ch, stream);
2178  break;

2787 #ifdef ARRAY
2788 prim P_arraysub() /* Array subscript calculation */
2789 { /* sub1 sub2 ... subn -- addr */
2790  int i, offset, esize, nsubs;
2791  stackitem *array;
2792  stackitem *isp;
2793 
2794  Sl(1);
2795  array = (((stackitem *) curword) + Dictwordl);
2796  Hpc(array);
2797  nsubs = *array++; /* Load number of subscripts */
2798  esize = *array++; /* Load element size */
2799 #ifndef NOMEMCHECK
2800  isp = &S0;
2801  for (i = 0; i < nsubs; i++) {
2802  stackitem subn = *isp--;
2803 
2804  if (subn < 0 || subn >= array[i])
2805  trouble("Subscript out of range");
2806  }
2807 #endif /* NOMEMCHECK */
2808  isp = &S0;
2809  offset = *isp; /* Load initial offset */
2810  for (i = 1; i < nsubs; i++)
2811  offset = (offset * (*(++array))) + *(--isp);
2812  Npop(nsubs - 1);
2813  /* Calculate subscripted address. We start at the current word,
2814  advance to the body, skip two more words for the subscript count
2815  and the fundamental element size, then skip the subscript bounds
2816  words (as many as there are subscripts). Then, finally, we
2817  can add the calculated offset into the array. */
2818  S0 = (stackitem) (((char *) (((stackitem *) curword) +
2819  Dictwordl + 2 + nsubs)) + (esize * offset));
2820 }

2822 prim P_array() /* Declare array */
2823 { /* sub1 sub2 ... subn n esize -- array */
2824  int i, nsubs, asize = 1;
2825  stackitem *isp;
2826 
2827  Sl(2);
2828 #ifndef NOMEMCHECK
2829  if (S0 <= 0)
2830  trouble("Bad array element size");
2831  if (S1 <= 0)
2832  trouble("Bad array subscript count");
2833 #endif /* NOMEMCHECK */
2834 
2835  nsubs = S1; /* Number of subscripts */
2836  Sl(nsubs + 2); /* Verify that dimensions are present */
2837 
2838  /* Calculate size of array as the product of the subscripts */
2839 
2840  asize = S0; /* Fundamental element size */
2841  isp = &S2;
2842  for (i = 0; i < nsubs; i++) {
2843 #ifndef NOMEMCHECK
2844  if (*isp <= 0)
2845  trouble("Bad array dimension");
2846 #endif /* NOMEMCHECK */
2847  asize *= *isp--;
2848  }
2849 
2850  asize = (asize + (sizeof(stackitem) - 1)) / sizeof(stackitem);
2851  Ho(asize + nsubs + 2); /* Reserve space for array and header */
2852  P_create(); /* Create variable */
2853  createword->wcode = P_arraysub; /* Set method to subscript calculate */
2854  Hstore = nsubs; /* Header <- Number of subscripts */
2855  Hstore = S0; /* Header <- Fundamental element size */
2856  isp = &S2;
2857  for (i = 0; i < nsubs; i++) { /* Header <- Store subscripts */
2858  Hstore = *isp--;
2859  }
2860  while (asize-- > 0) /* Clear the array to zero */
2861  Hstore = 0;
2862  Npop(nsubs + 2);
2863 }

3699 prim P_evaluate()
3700 { /* string -- status */
3701  int es = ATL_SNORM;
3702  atl_statemark mk;
3703  atl_int scomm = atl_comment; /* Stack comment pending state */
3704  dictword **sip = ip; /* Stack instruction pointer */
3705  char *sinstr = instream; /* Stack input stream */
3706  char *estring;
3707 
3708  Sl(1);
3709  Hpc(S0);
3710  estring = (char *) S0; /* Get string to evaluate */
3711  Pop; /* Pop so it sees arguments below it */
3712  atl_mark(&mk); /* Mark in case of error */
3713  ip = NULL; /* Fool atl_eval into interp state */
3714  if ((es = atl_eval(estring)) != ATL_SNORM) {
3715  atl_unwind(&mk);
3716  }
3717  /* If there were no other errors, check for a runaway comment. If
3718  we ended the file in comment-ignore mode, set the runaway comment
3719  error status and unwind the file. */
3720  if ((es == ATL_SNORM) && (atl_comment != 0)) {
3721  es = ATL_RUNCOMM;
3722  atl_unwind(&mk);
3723  }
3724  atl_comment = scomm; /* Unstack comment pending status */
3725  ip = sip; /* Unstack instruction pointer */
3726  instream = sinstr; /* Unstack input stream */
3727  So(1);
3728  Push = es; /* Return eval status on top of stack */
3729 }

4332 Exported void P_dodoes() /* Execute indirect call on method */
4333 {
4334  Rso(1);
4335  So(1);
4336  Rpush = ip; /* Push instruction pointer */
4337 #ifdef WALKBACK
4338  *wbptr++ = curword; /* Place word on walkback stack */
4339 #endif
4340  /* The compiler having craftily squirreled away the DOES> clause
4341  address before the word definition on the heap, we back up to
4342  the heap cell before the current word and load the pointer from
4343  there. This is an ABSOLUTE heap address, not a relative offset. */
4344  ip = *((dictword ***) (((stackitem *) curword) - 1));
4345 
4346  /* Push the address of this word's body as the argument to the
4347  DOES> clause. */
4348  Push = (stackitem) (((stackitem *) curword) + Dictwordl);
4349 }
4350 
4351 prim P_does() /* Specify method for word */
4352 {
4353 
4354  /* O.K., we were compiling our way through this definition and we've
4355  encountered the Dreaded and Dastardly Does. Here's what we do
4356  about it. The problem is that when we execute the word, we
4357  want to push its address on the stack and call the code for the
4358  DOES> clause by diverting the IP to that address. But...how
4359  are we to know where the DOES> clause goes without adding a
4360  field to every word in the system just to remember it. Recall
4361  that since this system is portable we can't cop-out through
4362  machine code. Further, we can't compile something into the
4363  word because the defining code may have already allocated heap
4364  for the word's body. Yukkkk. Oh well, how about this? Let's
4365  copy any and all heap allocated for the word down one stackitem
4366  and then jam the DOES> code address BEFORE the link field in
4367  the word we're defining.
4368 
4369  Then, when (DOES>) (P_dodoes) is called to execute the word, it
4370  will fetch that code address by backing up past the start of
4371  the word and seting IP to it. Note that FORGET must recognise
4372  such words (by the presence of the pointer to P_dodoes() in
4373  their wcode field, in case you're wondering), and make sure to
4374  deallocate the heap word containing the link when a
4375  DOES>-defined word is deleted. */
4376 
4377  if (createword != NULL) {
4378  stackitem *sp = ((stackitem *) createword), *hp;
4379 
4380  Rsl(1);
4381  Ho(1);
4382 
4383  /* Copy the word definition one word down in the heap to
4384  permit us to prefix it with the DOES clause address. */
4385 
4386  for (hp = hptr - 1; hp >= sp; hp--)
4387  *(hp + 1) = *hp;
4388  hptr++; /* Expand allocated length of word */
4389  *sp++ = (stackitem) ip; /* Store DOES> clause address before
4390  word's definition structure. */
4391  createword = (dictword *) sp; /* Move word definition down 1 item */
4392  createword->wcode = P_dodoes; /* Set code field to indirect jump */
4393 
4394  /* Now simulate an EXIT to bail out of the definition without
4395  executing the DOES> clause at definition time. */
4396 
4397  ip = R0; /* Set IP to top of return stack */
4398 #ifdef WALKBACK
4399  wbptr = (wbptr > wback) ? wbptr - 1 : wback;
4400 #endif
4401  Rpop; /* Pop the return stack */
4402  }
4403 }

4421  createword = NULL; /* Flag no word being created */

4702 #endif

4705 #else

4707 #endif

4711  break;

4715  }
4716 #ifdef EMBEDDED

4718 #endif
4719 #ifdef FREERTOS

4723 #endif
4724 }

4792 prim P_backresolve() /* Emit backward jump offset */
4793 {
4794  stackitem offset;
4795 
4796  Compiling;
4797  Sl(1);
4798  Ho(1);
4799  Hpc(S0);
4800  offset = -(hptr - (stackitem *) S0);
4801  Hstore = offset;
4802  Pop;
4803 }

4806 {
4807  Compiling;
4808  Ho(1);
4809  Push = (stackitem) hptr; /* Push heap address onto stack */
4810  Hstore = 0;
4811 }

4813 prim P_fwdresolve() /* Emit forward jump offset */
4814 {
4815  stackitem offset;
4816 
4817  Compiling;
4818  Sl(1);
4819  Hpc(S0);
4820  offset = (hptr - (stackitem *) S0);
4821  *((stackitem *) S0) = offset;
4822  Pop;
4823 }

5208 /* ATL_PRIMDEF -- Initialise the dictionary with the built-in primitive
5209  words. To save the memory overhead of separately
5210  allocated word items, we get one buffer for all
5211  the items and link them internally within the buffer. */
5212 
5213 void atl_primdef(pt)
5214  struct primfcn *pt;
5215 {
5216  struct primfcn *pf = pt;
5217  dictword *nw;
5218  int i, n = 0;
5219 #ifdef WORDSUSED
5220 #ifdef READONLYSTRINGS
5221  unsigned int nltotal;
5222  char *dynames, *cp;
5223 #endif /* READONLYSTRINGS */
5224 #endif /* WORDSUSED */
5225 
5226  /* Count the number of definitions in the table. */
5227 
5228  while (pf->pname != NULL) {
5229  n++;
5230  pf++;
5231  }
5232 
5233 #ifdef WORDSUSED
5234 #ifdef READONLYSTRINGS
5235  nltotal = n;
5236  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
5237  nltotal += strlen(pt[i].pname);
5238  }
5239  cp = dynames = alloc(nltotal);
5240  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
5241  strcpy(cp, pt[i].pname);
5242  cp += strlen(cp) + 1;
5243  }
5244  cp = dynames;
5245 #endif /* READONLYSTRINGS */
5246 #endif /* WORDSUSED */
5247 
5248  nw = (dictword *) alloc((unsigned int) (n * sizeof(dictword)));
5249 
5250  nw[n - 1].wnext = dict;
5251  dict = nw;
5252  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
5253  nw->wname = pt->pname;
5254 #ifdef WORDSUSED
5255 #ifdef READONLYSTRINGS
5256  nw->wname = cp;
5257  cp += strlen(cp) + 1;
5258 #endif /* READONLYSTRINGS */
5259 #endif /* WORDSUSED */
5260  nw->wcode = pt->pcode;
5261  if (i != (n - 1)) {
5262  nw->wnext = nw + 1;
5263  }
5264  nw++;
5265  pt++;
5266  }
5267 }

5271 /* PWALKBACK -- Print walkback trace. */
5272 
5273 static void pwalkback() {
5274  if (atl_walkback && ((curword != NULL) || (wbptr > wback))) {
5275 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5276  sprintf(outBuffer,"Walkback:\r\n"); // EMBEDDED
5277 #endif
5278 #ifdef FREERTOS
5279  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5280 #else
5281  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5282 #endif
5283 
5284  if (curword != NULL) {
5285 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5286  sprintf(outBuffer," %s\r\n", curword->wname + 1); // EMBEDDED
5287 #endif
5288 #ifdef FREERTOS
5289  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5290 #else
5291  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5292 #endif
5293  }
5294  while (wbptr > wback) {
5295  dictword *wb = *(--wbptr);
5296 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5297  sprintf(outBuffer," %s\r\n", wb->wname + 1); // EMBEDDED
5298 #endif
5299 #ifdef FREERTOS
5300  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5301 #else
5302  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5303 #endif
5304  }
5305  }
5306 }

5408 /* EXWORD -- Execute a word (and any sub-words it may invoke). */
5409 
5410 static void exword(wp)
5411  dictword *wp;
5412 {
5413  curword = wp;
5414 #ifdef TRACE
5415  if (atl_trace) {
5416 
5417  P_dots();
5418 #ifdef FREERTOS
5419  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)"\t\t") ;
5420 #else
5421  printf("\t\t");
5422 #endif

5424  sprintf(outBuffer,"\nTrace: %s ", curword->wname + 1); // EMBEDDED
5425 #endif
5426 #ifdef FREERTOS
5427 
5428  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5429  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)"\r\n") ;
5430 #else
5431  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5432 #endif
5433  }
5434 #endif /* TRACE */
5435  (*curword->wcode)(); /* Execute the first word */
5436  while (ip != NULL) {
5437 #ifdef BREAK
5438 #ifdef Keybreak
5439  Keybreak(); /* Poll for asynchronous interrupt */
5440 #endif
5441  if (broken) { /* Did we receive a break signal */
5442  trouble("Break signal");
5443  evalstat = ATL_BREAK;
5444  break;
5445  }
5446 #endif /* BREAK */
5447  curword = *ip++;
5448 #ifdef TRACE
5449  if (atl_trace) {
5450  P_dots();
5451 #ifdef FREERTOS
5452  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)"\t\t") ;
5453 #else
5454  printf("\t\t");
5455 #endif
5456 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5457  sprintf(outBuffer,"\nTrace: %s ", curword->wname + 1); // EMBEDDED
5458 #endif
5459 #ifdef FREERTOS
5460  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5461  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)"\r\n") ;
5462 #else
5463  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5464 #endif
5465  }
5466 #endif /* TRACE */
5467  (*curword->wcode)(); /* Execute the next word */
5468  }

5470 }

5472 /* ATL_INIT -- Initialise the ATLAST system. The dynamic storage areas
5473  are allocated unless the caller has preallocated buffers
5474  for them and stored the addresses into the respective
5475  pointers. In either case, the storage management
5476  pointers are initialised to the correct addresses. If
5477  the caller preallocates the buffers, it's up to him to
5478  ensure that the length allocated agrees with the lengths
5479  given by the atl_... cells. */

5485  dictprot = dict; /* Set protected mark in dictionary */

5488  save their compile addresses in static variables. */
5489

5491  Cconst(s_exit, "EXIT");

5524 #endif

5529  sizeof(dictword *));

5563  }

5565  so that pointer checking doesn't bounce references to it.
5566  When creating the heap, we preallocate this word and initialise
5567  the state to the interpretive state. */
5568  hptr = heap + 1;
5569  state = Falsity;
5570 #ifdef MEMSTAT
5571  heapmax = hptr;
5572 #endif
5573  heaptop = heap + atl_heaplen;
5574

5576  and variables built into the system. */
5577 
5578 #ifdef FILEIO
5579  { static struct {
5580  char *sfn;
5581  FILE *sfd;
5582  } stdfiles[] = {
5583  {"STDIN", NULL},

5585  {"STDERR", NULL}
5586  };

5606  }

5610  /*

5639 /* ATL_EXEC -- Execute a word, given its dictionary address. The
5640  evaluation status for that word's execution is
5641  returned. The in-progress evaluation status is
5642  preserved. */
5643 
5644 int atl_exec(dw)
5645  dictword *dw;
5646 {
5647  int sestat = evalstat, restat;
5648 
5649  evalstat = ATL_SNORM;
5650 #ifdef BREAK
5651  broken = False; /* Reset break received */
5652 #endif
5653 #undef Memerrs
5654 #define Memerrs evalstat
5655  Rso(1);
5656  Rpush = ip; /* Push instruction pointer */
5657  ip = NULL; /* Keep exword from running away */
5658  exword(dw);
5659  if (evalstat == ATL_SNORM) { /* If word ran to completion */
5660  Rsl(1);
5661  ip = R0; /* Pop the return stack */
5662  Rpop;
5663  }
5664 #undef Memerrs
5665 #define Memerrs
5666  restat = evalstat;
5667  evalstat = sestat;
5668  return restat;

5671 /* ATL_VARDEF -- Define a variable word. Called with the word's
5672  name and the number of bytes of storage to allocate
5673  for its body. All words defined with atl_vardef()
5674  have the standard variable action of pushing their
5675  body address on the stack when invoked. Returns
5676  the dictionary item for the new word, or NULL if
5677  the heap overflows. */
5678 
5679 dictword *atl_vardef(name, size)
5680  char *name;
5681  int size;
5682 {
5683  dictword *di;
5684  int isize = (size + (sizeof(stackitem) - 1)) / sizeof(stackitem);
5685 
5686 #undef Memerrs
5687 #define Memerrs NULL
5688  evalstat = ATL_SNORM;
5689  Ho(Dictwordl + isize);
5690 #undef Memerrs
5691 #define Memerrs
5692  if (evalstat != ATL_SNORM) /* Did the heap overflow */
5693  return NULL; /* Yes. Return NULL */
5694  createword = (dictword *) hptr; /* Develop address of word */
5695  createword->wcode = P_var; /* Store default code */
5696  hptr += Dictwordl; /* Allocate heap space for word */
5697  while (isize > 0) {
5698  Hstore = 0; /* Allocate heap area and clear it */
5699  isize--;
5700  }
5701  V strcpy(tokbuf, name); /* Use built-in token buffer... */
5702  ucase(tokbuf); /* so ucase() doesn't wreck arg string */
5703  enter(tokbuf); /* Make dictionary entry for it */
5704  di = createword; /* Save word address */
5705  createword = NULL; /* Mark no word underway */
5706  return di; /* Return new word */
5707 }

5720 /* ATL_UNWIND -- Restore system state to previously saved state. */
5721 
5722 void atl_unwind(mp)
5723  atl_statemark *mp;
5724 {
5725 
5726  /* If atl_mark() was called before the system was initialised, and
5727  we've initialised since, we cannot unwind. Just ignore the
5728  unwind request. The user must manually atl_init before an
5729  atl_mark() request is made. */
5730 
5731  if (mp->mdict == NULL) /* Was mark made before atl_init ? */
5732  return; /* Yes. Cannot unwind past init */
5733 
5734  stk = mp->mstack; /* Roll back stack allocation */
5735  hptr = mp->mheap; /* Reset heap state */
5736  rstk = mp->mrstack; /* Reset the return stack */
5737 
5738  /* To unwind the dictionary, we can't just reset the pointer,
5739  we must walk back through the chain and release all the name
5740  buffers attached to the items allocated after the mark was
5741  made. */
5742 
5743  while (dict != NULL && dict != dictprot && dict != mp->mdict) {
5744  free(dict->wname); /* Release name string for item */
5745  dict = dict->wnext; /* Link to previous item */
5746  }
5747 }

5753  exword() to halt after the current word. Since
5754  this can be called at any time, it daren't touch the
5755  system state directly, as it may be in an unstable
5756  condition. */
5757 
5758 void atl_break()
5759 {
5760  broken = True; /* Set break request */
5761 }

5764 /* ATL_LOAD -- Load a file into the system. */
5765 #ifdef FILEIO

5768 {

5770  char s[134];
5771  atl_statemark mk;
5772  atl_int scomm = atl_comment; /* Stack comment pending state */
5773  dictword **sip = ip; /* Stack instruction pointer */

5775  int lineno = 0; /* Current line number */
5776 
5777  atl_errline = 0; /* Reset line number of error */

5779  ip = NULL; /* Fool atl_eval into interp state */
5780  while (atl_fgetsp(s, 132, fp) != NULL) {
5781  lineno++;
5782  if ((es = atl_eval(s)) != ATL_SNORM) {
5783  atl_errline = lineno; /* Save line number of error */
5784  atl_unwind(&mk);
5785  break;

5787  }

5789  we ended the file in comment-ignore mode, set the runaway comment

5791  if ((es == ATL_SNORM) && (atl_comment == Truth)) {
5792 #ifdef MEMMESSAGE
5793 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5794  sprintf(outBuffer,"\nRunaway `(' comment.\n"); // EMBEDDED
5795 #endif

5798 #else
5799  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5800 #endif
5801 #endif

5807  instream = sinstr; /* Unstack input stream */

5809 }
5810 #endif

5857 /* ATL_EVAL -- Evaluate a string containing ATLAST words. */
5858 
5859 int atl_eval(char *sp) {
5860  int i;
5861 
5862 #undef Memerrs
5863 #define Memerrs evalstat
5864  instream = sp;
5865  evalstat = ATL_SNORM; /* Set normal evaluation status */
5866 #ifdef BREAK
5867  broken = False; /* Reset asynchronous break */
5868 #endif
5869 
5870  /* If automatic prologue processing is configured and we haven't yet
5871  initialised, check if this is a prologue statement. If so, execute
5872  it. Otherwise automatically initialise with the memory specifications
5873  currently operative. */
5874 
5875 #ifdef PROLOGUE
5876  if (dict == NULL) {
5877  if (atl_prologue(sp))
5878  return evalstat;
5879  atl_init();
5880  }
5881 #endif /* PROLOGUE */
5882 
5883  while ((evalstat == ATL_SNORM) && (i = token(&instream)) != TokNull) {
5884  dictword *di;
5885 
5886  switch (i) {
5887  case TokWord:
5888  if (forgetpend) {
5889  forgetpend = False;
5890  ucase(tokbuf);
5891  if ((di = lookup(tokbuf)) != NULL) {
5892  dictword *dw = dict;
5893 
5894  /* Pass 1. Rip through the dictionary to make sure
5895  this word is not past the marker that
5896  guards against forgetting too much. */
5897 
5898  while (dw != NULL) {
5899  if (dw == dictprot) {
5900 #ifdef MEMMESSAGE
5901 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5902  sprintf(outBuffer,"\nForget protected.\n"); // EMBEDDED
5903 #endif
5904 #ifdef FREERTOS
5905  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5906 #else
5907  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5908 #endif
5909 #endif
5910  evalstat = ATL_FORGETPROT;
5911  di = NULL;
5912  }
5913  if (strcmp(dw->wname + 1, tokbuf) == 0)
5914  break;
5915  dw = dw->wnext;
5916  }
5917 
5918  /* Pass 2. Walk back through the dictionary
5919  items until we encounter the target
5920  of the FORGET. Release each item's
5921  name buffer and dechain it from the
5922  dictionary list. */
5923 
5924  if (di != NULL) {
5925  do {
5926  dw = dict;
5927  if (dw->wname != NULL)
5928  free(dw->wname);
5929  dict = dw->wnext;
5930  } while (dw != di);
5931  /* Finally, back the heap allocation pointer
5932  up to the start of the last item forgotten. */
5933  hptr = (stackitem *) di;
5934  /* Uhhhh, just one more thing. If this word
5935  was defined with DOES>, there's a link to
5936  the method address hidden before its
5937  wnext field. See if it's a DOES> by testing
5938  the wcode field for P_dodoes and, if so,
5939  back up the heap one more item. */
5940  if (di->wcode == (codeptr) P_dodoes) {
5941 #ifdef FORGETDEBUG
5942 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5943  sprintf(outBuffer," Forgetting DOES> word. "); // EMBEDDED
5944 #endif
5945 #ifdef FREERTOS
5946  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5947 #else
5948  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5949 #endif
5950 #endif
5951  hptr--;
5952  }
5953  }
5954  } else {
5955 #ifdef MEMMESSAGE
5956 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5957  sprintf(outBuffer," '%s' undefined ", tokbuf); // EMBEDDED
5958 #endif
5959 #ifdef FREERTOS
5960  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5961 #else
5962  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5963 #endif
5964 #endif
5965  evalstat = ATL_UNDEFINED;
5966  }
5967  } else if (tickpend) {
5968  tickpend = False;
5969  ucase(tokbuf);
5970  if ((di = lookup(tokbuf)) != NULL) {
5971  So(1);
5972  Push = (stackitem) di; /* Push word compile address */
5973  } else {
5974 #ifdef MEMMESSAGE
5975 #ifdef EMBEDDED
5976  sprintf(outBuffer," '%s' undefined ", tokbuf); // EMBEDDED
5977 #endif
5978 #ifdef FREERTOS
5979  atlastTxBuffer(console, (uint8_t *)outBuffer) ;
5980 #else
5981  printf("%s",outBuffer);
5982 #endif
5983 #endif
5984  evalstat = ATL_UNDEFINED;
5985  }
5986  } else if (defpend) {
5987  /* If a definition is pending, define the token and
5988  leave the address of the new word item created for
5989  it on the return stack. */
5990  defpend = False;
5991  ucase(tokbuf);
5992  if (atl_redef && (lookup(tokbuf) != NULL)) {
5993 #ifdef EMBEDDED
